"ENG-102-5500" and "WX1516_V00" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos.
The device is shown '''SparkLAN''' branded in the FCC photos. '''Wireless Multi-mode AP''' is the tagline under the '''SparkLAN''' logo on the front of the device. :The FCC test report states that the FCC ID also covers the [[SparkLAN WX-1520|'''SparkLAN''' WX-1520]].
The default SSID ''may'' be '''default'''.
Presumed 00:90:4B ('''Gemtek''') OUI - it's on the FCC EUT's label in the external photos.
The power adapter shown in the FCC photos is a '''Delta''' ADP-10SB REV. H (100-240VAC ~ 50-60Hz, 0.4A -> 5VDC, 2A).
